Various persons witnessing the recent San Francisco earthquake conveyed their reactions as  follows: "It's like a blind man trying to feel an elephant.
We're just now figuring out bits and pieces of  this disaster."
(Member, California Seismic Safety Commission) "Usually earthquakes pass, but this one went on and on.
It just wouldn't stop..It was very, very  bad."
(Schoolteacher, Silicon Valley) "At first I thought the smoke was fog.
Then I could see a big ball of flame."
(Driver, coming  from Sonoma) "This upper deck was absolutely shaking, the light stanchions were blowing back and forth."
(Reporter, World Series) 
